********>Bugfix 1:

Authors:  Trent E. Balius and Scott Brozell.

Date:  September 22, 2025

Program:  dock6

Description:  In orienting the ligand, include in a matching clique the case of
an identical receptor sphere and ligand atom pair.  This bug was exposed when
ligand atoms were used to generate receptor spheres:  When comparing the
results for the reference ligand to those for a translated reference ligand,
the translated ligand had more generated matches.

Fix:  make the changes to the indicated files below:
This is most simply accomplished with the commands:
cd $DOCK_HOME; patch -N -p0 < bugfix.1
cd install; make dock; make test

